Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the onion to the ovenproof pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir through the @risotto rice{175%g}, garlic and @mixed herbs{1%sachet}. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @boiled water{600%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your #oven{} until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} to clean and dry it with a #paper towel{}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins.

While the courgette is frying, zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Transfer your charred courgette into a medium-sized #bowl{}, add a good squeeze of lemon, lemon zest and the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.

Season and set aside to marinate.

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Chop into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the now-empty frying pan on medium heat.

Once hot, add the asparagus and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of water and immediately cover with a lid or some foil.

Cook until the asparagus is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the @pesto{32%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @butter{20%g}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Stir through the marinated courgette.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and lemon juice if you feel it needs it.

Share your risotto between your serving plates.

Scatter the asparagus on top of your risotto to finish.

Enjoy!